From 8e4392c5231378079346df657ba7cbdacbeacaa6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: KITOHSY <hongsun900912@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 27 May 2026 00:09:38 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 11/12] T15: add ScNotificationClient + extend pairing response
 with reservation context
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- ScNotificationClient: polls Broker GET /api/v1/notifications every 10s with
  the connect-token Bearer (verify-only on the broker side, multi-use until
  reservation.ends_at), emits notificationReceived per pending modal, and
  exposes ackNotification + postExplicitEnd for the modal channel return path.
- ScBrokerClient::pairingRelayed signal extended to carry reservationId +
  endsAt — broker T15 added these to the /api/v1/pairing response so the
  client can wire up notification polling without an extra round-trip.
- NvComputer: ephemeral pendingReservationId / pendingEndsAt members
  (mirroring the T13/T14 pending* fields, persistence-excluded).
- ComputerManager::scHandleBrokerPairingRelayed stashes those onto the
  pending NvComputer under the lock; scClearPendingConnect clears them too.

Session integration (constructor extension, ScNotificationClient lifecycle,
SDL modal UI, Ctrl+Alt+Shift+Q confirm-on-quit interception) lands in a
follow-up patch — those require Qt build + manual e2e and are tracked in
client-patches/moonlight-qt/BUILD.md.
